Using `react-laflet 2.3.0` a map is rendered and polylines are drawn according to co-ordinates data received via props. 

onmouseover of polyline opens up a popup (MUICard) and shows data by making a REST call in `componentDidMount` of `MUICard`. So far so good.

Whenever changed props are received by map component, polylines are added or removed and some of them stays depending on the data received.
 
On these old polylines, onmouseover event opens a popup with **stale data**. No request is fired which can be seen in debug window of browser. Is it caused by javascript&#39;s `pass by reference` or caching by browser?


Below is the code from render method of map component.

```
 render() {
    
    const lineData = this.props.data; 
   
    return (
    &lt;div id=&quot;map&quot;&gt;
      &lt;Map
          style={{ height: &quot;80vh&quot;, width: &#39;100%&#39;}}
          center={position}
          zoom={this.props.zoom}
          ref=&#39;mapRef&#39;
        &gt;
      &lt;TileLayer
            url=&quot;https://cartodb-basemaps-{s}.global.ssl.fastly.net/dark_all/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png&quot;
            attribution=&#39;&amp;copy; &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright&quot;&gt;OpenStreetMap&lt;/a&gt; &amp;copy; &lt;a href=&quot;http://cartodb.com/attributions&quot;&gt;CartoDB&lt;/a&gt;&#39; 
            
      /&gt;
      {
        lineData.map((line, index) =&gt; {
        return &lt;Polyline key={index} positions={[
        [line.fromY, line.fromX], [line.toY, line.toX],
        ]} weight={&#39;0.80&#39;} color={&#39;red&#39;}
        onMouseOver={e =&gt; e.target.openPopup()}       
      &gt;
        &lt;Popup &gt;                
          &lt;MUICard poiId={line.poi_id} /&gt;                
        &lt;/Popup&gt;
      &lt;/Polyline&gt;
      })
    }
      &lt;/Map&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    );
  }
```

How to ensure that onmouseover event for each polyline ends up with REST call resulting into fresh data in popup? or simply putting, 
